==Greek==
Greek: όπα/ Roman: Upa

===Etymology===
Probably from Turkish ''hopla'' originally meaning jump, hop, or dance.  Of expressive origin.

===Pronunciation===
ŏŏpä

====Interjection====
# Used as a shout of approval, triumph, encouragement or excitement as ''[[olé]]!''
# Used as a command to stop, or as an expression of surprise as ''[[whoa]]!''

====Noun====
'''όπα'''

# A cry of ''upa!''

===Alternative spellings===
Also upa, oopa, umpa, oompa.

